com.wingfoot.xml.schema
Class SchemaHolder

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.wingfoot.xml.schema.SchemaHolder
All Implemented Interfaces:
XMLHolder
public class SchemaHolder
extends java.lang.Object
implements XMLHolder

Encapsulates the properties of a well formed XML schema. A XML schema has many individual components. The get and set methods allow for addition or removal of components from the schema.

isAttributeQualified

public boolean isAttributeQualified()
Returns true if locally declared attributes are to be qualified; false otherwise.

setAttributeQualified

public void setAttributeQualified(boolean newIsAttributeQualified)
Sets the attributeFormDefault attribute in the <schema> element. If set to true (default behavior) then all locally declared attributes in the instance is qualified with namespace. If set to false the locally declared attributes are not qualified.

For better interoperability, it is recommended that this be set to true.

Parameters:
newIsAttributeQualified - true if local attributes are to be qualified with namespace; false otherwise.

isElementQualified

public boolean isElementQualified()
Returns true if locally declared attributes are to be qualified; false otherwise.

setElementQualified

public void setElementQualified(boolean newIsElementQualified)
Sets the elementFormDefault attribute in the <schema> element. If set to true (default behavior) then all locally declared elements in the instance is qualified with namespace. If set to false the locally declared elements are not qualified.

For better interoperability, it is recommended that this be set to true.

Parameters:
newIsElementQualified - true if local elements are to be qualified with namespace; false otherwise.

setImport

public void setImport(java.lang.String namespace,
                      java.lang.String location)
Limited support is available for schema imports. This methods allows for specifying the namespace and location of the schema. This appears as part of <import> element in the schema definition.

If an attempt is made to add a duplicate namespace, the operation fails.

Parameters:
namespace - the namespace to associate with the schema.
location - the physical location of the schema.

getImport

public java.util.Vector getImport()
Returns a Vector of imported schemas if any was specified.
Returns:
Vector of schemas. Each element of the Vector is a String[]. Index 0 contains the namespace and index 1 contains the location; returns null if no schema import was specified.

getNormalizedAttribute

public Attribute getNormalizedAttribute(Attribute refAttribute)
Given a Attribute (a Component) that is a reference to another to another attribute, retrieves the Attribute that is being referred to.

If the refAttribute is not a reference then refAttribute is returned back.

If refAttribute is null or if the reference to the attribute is not present in this SchemaHolder, null is returned.

If the referenced attribute is present in this SchemaHolder then the referenced Attribute is returned.

Parameters:
refAttribute - Attribute that has a ref element in it.
Returns:
Attribute the referenced Attribute.

If the refAttribute is not a reference then refAttribute is returned back.

If refAttribute is null or if the reference to the attribute is not present in this SchemaHolder, null is returned.

Parameters:
